      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُهُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ أَصَابَ دَابَّةً قَدْ سُرِقَتْ مِنْ جَارٍ لَهُ فَأَخَذَهَا لِيَأْتِيَهُ بِهَا فَنَفَقَتْ قَالَ \"لَيْسَ عَلَيْهِ شَيْءٌ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3541 - Al-Hasan ibn Mahbub narrated from Al-Hasan ibn Salih, from Abu Abdullah (as). He said: I asked him about a man who found a stolen animal that belonged to his neighbor, so he took it to return it to him, but the animal died.\nImam (as) said: \"There is nothing (no liability) upon him.\""
        ]
      }
